{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-03-29T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Peggy's Cove is a small yet captivating village on the rugged coast of Nova Scotia that offers a glimpse of life by the sea. The village's most famous landmark is Peggy's Point Lighthouse—also known as Peggy's Cove Lighthouse—first established in 1868 and replaced by the current structure in 1915. For over a century, it has guided ships through the ever-changing Atlantic waters, serving as a timeless symbol of coastal life. The surrounding landscape, with its windswept beauty and crashing waves, feels almost untouched by time.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PeggysLighthouse_ROW0925207018_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PeggysLighthouse_ROW0925207018_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Peggy's Point Lighthouse, Atlantic Coast, Nova Scotia, Canada","Copyright":"© Prashanth Bala/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260329_PeggysLighthouse\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Peggys+Point+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260329_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260329_PeggysLighthouse"},"Ssd":"20260329","Name":"PeggysLighthouse","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0925207018","FullDateString":"29. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The African buffalo, a powerful and imposing creature, roams the savannas and wetlands of Tanzania, particularly within the Ngorongoro Conservation Area (NCA). Known for their large, curved horns and massive size, they are one of Africa's 'Big Five' (buffalo, elephant, leopard, rhino, lion) and are widely respected for their strength and resilience. The NCA, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, offers a dramatic and ecologically rich setting for observing these formidable herbivores.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.CapeBuffalo_ROW0708366233_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.CapeBuffalo_ROW0708366233_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"African buffalo, Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania","Copyright":"© jesuss8/500px/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260328_CapeBuffalo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=African+buffalo&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260328_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260328_CapeBuffalo"},"Ssd":"20260328","Name":"CapeBuffalo","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0708366233","FullDateString":"28. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"This is the kind of landscape that makes maps feel suddenly more interesting. Evening settles quietly over Maligne Lake in Jasper National Park, Alberta. As temperatures drop, the surface stills, mirroring snow-dusted peaks that formed during the last Ice Age. Stretching about 22 kilometres, the lake owes its existence to glacial movement that carved the valley and left behind meltwater basins. Today, cold, oxygen-rich freshwater sustains ecosystems that include species such as lake trout and mountain whitefish. Boat cruises and paddling routes offer one of the best ways to view Spirit Island, the small but widely photographed landmark featured in the image.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_ROW4443502358_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AuroraIsland_ROW4443502358_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Aurora over Spirit Island on Maligne Lake, Jasper National Park, Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© Mumemories/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260327_AuroraIsland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Maligne+Lake+Canada&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260327_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260327_AuroraIsland"},"Ssd":"20260327","Name":"AuroraIsland","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4443502358","FullDateString":"27. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Running along the remote southwest coast of Vancouver Island, the West Coast Trail is one of the country's most legendary hikes. Located in British Columbia's Pacific Rim National Park Reserve, the trail stretches about 76 kilometres through rainforest, beaches and rocky shoreline. It was established in 1907 as a lifesaving route for shipwreck survivors along what sailors once called the 'Graveyard of the Pacific.'","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LoganCreek_ROW8107496948_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LoganCreek_ROW8107496948_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Logan Creek Suspension Bridge, West Coast Trail, British Columbia, Canada","Copyright":"© Tandem Stock/Adobe Stock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260326_LoganCreek\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=West+Coast+Trail+hike&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260326_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260326_LoganCreek"},"Ssd":"20260326","Name":"LoganCreek","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8107496948","FullDateString":"26. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Manatees may seem slow and sleepy, but they have some surprising tricks under the surface. For starters, they are one of the few mammals that constantly replace their teeth. As old molars wear down from chewing gritty seagrass, new ones slowly roll forward like a conveyor belt—handy for an animal that eats for up to eight hours a day.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ManateeSpring_ROW7760366755_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ManateeSpring_ROW7760366755_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Juvenile manatees in a freshwater spring, Crystal River, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Gregory Sweeney/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260325_ManateeSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Manatee&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260325_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260325_ManateeSpring"},"Ssd":"20260325","Name":"ManateeSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7760366755","FullDateString":"25. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When mist drifts across Königssee Lake, located in Bavaria, Germany, in the early morning, the landscape feels almost timeless. The long, narrow mountain lake lies in south-eastern Bavaria, cradled between the steep rock faces of the Berchtesgaden Alps. Large parts of the lake lie within Berchtesgaden National Park, Germany's only Alpine national park, where nature is largely allowed to develop without human interference.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KoenigsseeFog_ROW4902303534_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KoenigsseeFog_ROW4902303534_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Königssee Lake, Bavaria, Germany","Copyright":"© EyeEm Mobile GmbH/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260324_KoenigsseeFog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Konigssee+Lake+Bavaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260324_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260324_KoenigsseeFog"},"Ssd":"20260324","Name":"KoenigsseeFog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"4902303534","FullDateString":"24. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The strength of nature is nowhere more evident than in powerful storms. Scary? Yes. Fascinating? Even more so. Learning to understand and respect these forces is how people learn to live alongside them. The image of lightning over saguaro cacti captures that balance perfectly. The Sonoran Desert, spanning 260,000 square kilometres across the United States and Mexico, may appear dry and still, but it hosts one of North America's most dynamic desert climates.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_ROW5466478182_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SonoranStorm_ROW5466478182_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lightning storm over saguaro cacti, Sonoran Desert, Arizona, United States","Copyright":"© Jack Dykinga/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sonoran+Desert+Arizona&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260323_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260323_SonoranStorm"},"Ssd":"20260323","Name":"SonoranStorm","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5466478182","FullDateString":"23. maalisk. 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ever wondered what a high-mountain lake looks like before the hikers arrive? At over 1,940 metres above sea level, Lake Gentau sits quietly in the Pyrenees of south-west France, its cold waters reflecting granite slopes and shifting clouds. Reached on foot from the Ossau Valley, the lake has long been a pause point for shepherds and walkers crossing these summer pastures. Look up and you will spot the dark volcanic shape of Pic du Midi d'Ossau nearby. Why does that peak matter? For centuries it served as a natural landmark guiding travellers through the mountain passes between France and Spain. Today it sits near the western boundary of the Pyrenees National Park. On calm days the surface turns mirror-still, reflecting sky, rock and the sharp outline of the Ossau peak. Not a bad reward for a mountain walk.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.LacGentau_ROW3338740451_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.LacGentau_ROW3338740451_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Lake Gentau in the French Pyrenees, Pyrénées-Atlantiques, France","Copyright":"© MICHAUX Stéphane/Hemis.fr/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260405_LacGentau\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lake+Gentau+French+Pyrenees&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260405_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260405_LacGentau"},"Ssd":"20260405","Name":"LacGentau","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3338740451","FullDateString":"5. huhtik. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Before sunrise, the moorland clock punches in—and the dance floor opens. Male black grouse don't send invites; they boom them. Welcome to lekking season, where romance is competitive, noisy and strictly outdoors.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GrouseGuff_ROW0536575976_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GrouseGuff_ROW0536575976_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Black grouse males facing off on a lekking site, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260404_GrouseGuff\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Black+grouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260404_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260404_GrouseGuff"},"Ssd":"20260404","Name":"GrouseGuff","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0536575976","FullDateString":"4. huhtik. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Some bridges in Amsterdam just get you across a canal. The Armbrug does more—it seems to wave hello as you pass. Nestled over the Oudezijds Voorburgwal canal, its name, meaning 'arm bridge,' refers to the nearby Oudezijds Armsteeg (Old Side Arm Alley), not a literal limb, but it's easy to imagine it greeting cyclists and pedestrians along the way.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArmbrugBridge_ROW0384861076_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArmbrugBridge_ROW0384861076_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Armbrug bridge, Amsterdam, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Alexander Spatari/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260403_ArmbrugBridge\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Armbrug+bridge+Amsterdam&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260403_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260403_ArmbrugBridge"},"Ssd":"20260403","Name":"ArmbrugBridge","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0384861076","FullDateString":"3. huhtik. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring announces itself across California's Central Valley with the first bursts of wildflowers following the winter rains. Stretching about 720 kilometres from north to south and covering approximately 51,800 square kilometres, the valley is one of the world's most productive agricultural regions. In early spring, however, an older identity briefly resurfaces. From March through April, native annuals such as goldfields, tidy tips and owl's clover quickly germinate once temperature and soil moisture are optimal. They race to complete their life cycles before the long dry season begins.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WildflowerValley_ROW2763453477_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WildflowerValley_ROW2763453477_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Wildflower bloom, Central Valley, California, United States","Copyright":"© Jeff Lewis/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260402_WildflowerValley\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Central+Valley+California&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260402_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260402_WildflowerValley"},"Ssd":"20260402","Name":"WildflowerValley","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2763453477","FullDateString":"2. huhtik. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today, let's hop into the world of one of nature's smallest yet most hardworking ambassadors. Frogs may not wear crowns—unless you believe in Frog Kings—but they do rule quietly behind the scenes. By keeping insect populations in check, they help ecosystems stay balanced. Even more impressive? Their sensitive skin also means they react quickly to changes in their surroundings, which is why scientists often look at frogs to understand the health of wetlands and forests. Talk about living barometers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.JapaneseTreeFrog_ROW2089186925_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.JapaneseTreeFrog_ROW2089186925_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Japanese tree frog in a pink morning glory","Copyright":"© Tetsuya Tanooka/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260401_JapaneseTreeFrog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Japanese+tree+frog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260401_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260401_JapaneseTreeFrog"},"Ssd":"20260401","Name":"JapaneseTreeFrog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2089186925","FullDateString":"1. huhtik. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Paradise Cave makes a powerful first impression the moment visitors step inside. This vast limestone cavern lies deep within Phong Nha-Ke Bang National Park in central Vietnam, a region marked by rugged mountains and countless hidden caves. Stretching 31 kilometres, Paradise Cave is one of Asia's longest dry caves, and its scale is immediately apparent. High ceilings rise above the walkways and layered patterns formed by mineral-rich water over millions of years line the walls.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ParadiseCave_ROW1547496612_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ParadiseCave_ROW1547496612_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Paradise Cave, Phong Nha-Ke Bang National Park, Vietnam","Copyright":"© Pakawat Thongcharoen/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260331_ParadiseCave\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Paradise+Cave+Vietnam&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260331_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260331_ParadiseCave"},"Ssd":"20260331","Name":"ParadiseCave","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1547496612","FullDateString":"31. maalisk. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The demoiselle crane is a small yet striking migratory bird found across Central Asia, from its breeding grounds in the steppes of Kazakhstan, Mongolia and northern China, to its wintering grounds in India, Nepal and parts of Africa. With its elegant appearance—slender neck, long legs and beautiful plumage—it is often considered one of the most graceful crane species. They are known for their intricate courtship dances, during which pairs engage in synchronized movements and calls, creating a beautiful spectacle.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.IndiaCranes_ROW8052837107_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.IndiaCranes_ROW8052837107_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Demoiselle cranes, India","Copyright":"© Axel Gomille/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260330_IndiaCranes\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Demoiselle+cranes&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260330_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260330_IndiaCranes"},"Ssd":"20260330","Name":"IndiaCranes","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8052837107","FullDateString":"30. maalisk. 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Päivän kuva","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Lisätietoja","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Lahjoita nyt","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Pikatieto:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Uusimmat kotisivukuvat","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Kotisivukuva {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"Historiallisia tapahtumia tällä päivämäärällä","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Tänä päivänä {0} {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Jaa tämän päivän Bing-aloitussivu","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Lataa tämä kuva. Kuvaa saa käyttää vain taustakuvana.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Lataa tämä kuva","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"Tätä kuvaa ei voi ladata taustakuvaksi.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TEXT":"Tiedot","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK":"https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2127455","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK_TEXT":"Hanki Bing-taustakuvasovellus","LOC_BING_APP_TEXT":"Ha